## MongoDB Atlas Setup (Required for all cloud deployments)

1. Create free account at [mongodb.com/atlas](https://www.mongodb.com/atlas)
2. Create free cluster (M0 tier)
3. Create database user (username/password)
4. Network Access → Add IP whitelist (`0.0.0.0/0` for all IPs)
5. Get connection string:
   - Cluster → Connect → Connect your application
   - Copy URI: `mongodb+srv://<user>:<password>@cluster.mongodb.net/Traveloop?retryWrites=true&w=majority`

---

## Environment Variables for Production

Create `.env` file in `backend/` directory:

```env
# Server
PORT=3000
NODE_ENV=production

# MongoDB
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://user:password@cluster.mongodb.net/Traveloop

# JWT
JWT_SECRET=your-long-random-string-min-32-chars
JWT_EXPIRE=7d

# Frontend URL (for CORS)
FRONTEND_URL=https://your-frontend-domain.com
```

